s%20costing%20some%20Americans%20up%20to%20%24120%2C000%20in%20retirement%20savings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Young%20man%20in%20a%20suit%20walking%20on%20Wall%20Street%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fc9218e1443b8dc48e2bc4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222655%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ENYSE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPaying%20off%20low-interest%20debt%20early%20can%20cost%20you%20retirement%20savings%2C%20Vanguard%20says.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMissing%20out%20on%20401(k)%20matches%20while%20paying%20down%20low%20interest%20debt%20could%20reduce%20retirement%20funds%20by%20up%20to%20%24120%2C000.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EVanguard%20recommends%20paying%20down%20high-interest%20debt%20quickly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThinking%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftook-20-years-100-000-pay-off-student-loans-early-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epaying%20off%20your%20student%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20early%3F%20Vanguard%20says%20doing%20so%20could%20cost%20you%20big%20time%20in%20retirement%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaying%20off%20debt%20early%20might%20seem%20like%20a%20smart%20move%2C%20as%20you%20save%20on%20future%20interest%20payments%20and%20enjoy%20the%20peace%20of%20mind%20that%20comes%20with%20being%20debt-free.%20But%20doing%20so%20should%20depend%20on%20the%20interest%20rate%20on%20your%20debt%2C%20the%20asset%20management%20giant%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20recent%20study%2C%20Vanguard%20said%20that%20low-interest%20debt%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20can%20be%20costly%20to%20pay%20off%20early.%20That's%20because%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20investors%20who%20are%20paying%20down%20their%20debt%20ahead%20of%20schedule%20are%20not%20taking%20their%20full%20employer%20401(k)%20matches%2C%20the%20firm%20found.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20the%20percentage%20of%20investors%20not%20taking%20their%20full%20match%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-paid-my-mortgage-off-early-sometimes-i-regret-it-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epaying%20off%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20auto%20loans%2C%20and%20student%20loans%20early%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221412%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22401k%20match%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a0cbe05ce0a5b2f12d7d883%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EVanguard%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20consequences%20of%20this%20mistake%20are%20potentially%20quite%20large%2C%20with%20prepayers%20missing%20out%20on%20almost%20%241%2C100%20per%20year%2C%20on%20average%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20report%20from%20the%20firm%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20long%20term%2C%20prepaying%20a%20debt%20for%2010%20years%20while%20failing%20to%20get%20the%20full%20benefit%20of%20the%20match%20during%20that%20time%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20estimated%20%24120%2C000%20less%20at%20retirement%20age.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndy%20Reed%2C%20Vanguard's%20head%20of%20behavioral%20economics%20research%20and%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20report%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20missing%20a%20401(k)%20employer%20match%20is%20harmful%20in%20a%20couple%20of%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you're%2025%20and%20you're%20giving%20up%20free%20match%20dollars%20and%20you've%20got%20a%2040-year%20career%20ahead%20of%20you%2C%20it's%20a%20long%20time%20for%20not%20only%20the%20match%2C%20which%20is%20an%20immediate%20return%20if%20you%20will%2C%20but%20also%20the%20compounding%20on%20the%20match%20dollars%20is%20absolutely%20massive%20over%20an%20extended%20time%20period%2C%26quot%3B%20Reed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20paying%20off%20a%20mortgage%20early%20instead%20of%20taking%20an%20employer%20match%2C%20concentration%20in%20real-estate%20in%20one's%20investment%20portfolio%20can%20be%20another%20negative%20consequence%2C%20Vanguard%20said.%20Investing%20excess%20cash%20in%20the%20market%2C%20therefore%2C%20may%20be%20a%20more%20prudent%20approach%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPre-payment%20increases%20when%20people%20are%20in%20their%2050s%20and%2060%2C%20the%20study%20showed%2C%20as%20they%20earn%20more%20and%20near%20the%20end%20of%20their%20payment%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20common%20money%20mistake%20Vanguard%20sees%20people%20make%20is%20paying%20down%20high-interest%20debt%20too%20slowly.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhid-credit-card-debt-told-fiance-money-shame-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECredit%20card%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20auto%20loans%20tend%20to%20have%20higher%20interest%20rates%20and%20are%20usually%20the%20type%20of%20debt%20one%20should%20focus%20on%20first%2C%20Reed%20said%2C%20while%20mortgage%20and%20student%20loans%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20manageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20each%20person's%20financial%20situation%20is%20different%2C%20Reed%20said%20that%20obvious%20annualized%20interest%20rates%20to%20try%20to%20pay%20off%20early%20are%20over%2020%25%2C%20while%20obvious%20ones%20to%20probably%20not%20pay%20off%20early%20are%20under%204%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20designing%20a%20repayment%20approach%20depends%20on%20the%20individual%2C%20Reed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20I'm%20seeking%20peace%20of%20mind%2C%20right%3F%20Living%20in%20a%20paid-off%20house%20is%20a%20great%20source%20of%20peace%20of%20mind%2C%20potentially%2C%26quot%3B%20Reed%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BWe%20just%20want%20people%20to%20know%2C%20hey%2C%20there%20is%20a%20cost%20to%20that%20peace%20of%20mind%2C%20and%20as%20long%20as%20they're%20willing%20to%2C%20to%20kind%20of%20pay%20the%20price%20for%20the%20peace%20of%20mind%2C%20then%20it%20could%20be%20the%20right%20choice%20for%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http