r%22%3A%22TOI%20Entertainment%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sam%20Altman%20says%20he's%20'delighted%20to%20be%20wrong'%20about%20AI%20destroying%20white-collar%20jobs%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227248%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sam%20Altman%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a158a4ab1025a62a5c87278%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman.%3Cp%3ETayfun%20Coskun%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESam%20Altman%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20has%20previously%20said%20AI%20would%20wipe%20out%20%26quot%3Bentire%20classes%26quot%3B%20of%20jobs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20week%2C%20he%20said%20he%20had%20been%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20wrong%26quot%3B%20about%20some%20of%20his%20AI%20predictions%20about%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESome%20companies%20have%20cited%20AI%20during%20layoffs%2C%20but%20a%20jobs%20apocalypse%20has%20not%20happened.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20jobs%20apocalypse%20has%20not%20yet%20come%20to%20pass%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Sam%20Altman%20says%20he's%20happy%20to%20be%20wrong%20about%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20OpenAI%20boss%20told%20a%20tech%20conference%20this%20week%20that%20his%20predictions%20about%20AI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-changing-entry-level-work-advice-to-succeed-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewiping%20out%20entry-level%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20been%20wide%20of%20the%20mark%2C%20after%20once%20suggesting%20that%20the%20technology%20would%20cause%20%26quot%3Bentire%20classes%26quot%3B%20of%20jobs%20to%20disappear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20scorecard%2C%20at%20the%20highest%20level%2C%20would%20be%20we've%20been%20roughly%20right%20on%20technological%20predictions%20and%20pretty%20wrong%20on%20the%20social%20and%20economic%20implications%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Altman%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commbank.com.au%2Farticles%2Fnewsroom%2F2026%2F05%2Fsam-altman-close-ai-gap.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esummary%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20conversation%20with%20Matt%20Comyn%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Commonwealth%20Bank%20of%20Australia%2C%20published%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20OpenAI%20CEO%20said%20that%20the%20short-term%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20entry-level%20white-collar%20jobs%20had%20not%20been%20anywhere%20near%20as%20bad%20as%20he%20once%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20delighted%20to%20be%20wrong%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20following%20the%20release%20of%20ChatGPT%20in%202022%2C%20Altman%20was%20among%20several%20AI%20executives%20who%20warned%20that%20the%20technology%20would%20spark%20serious%20upheaval%20in%20the%20job%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202023%20interview%20with%20The%20Atlantic%2C%20he%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bjobs%20are%20definitely%20going%20to%20go%20away%26quot%3B%20as%20companies%20embrace%20AI%2C%20but%20added%20that%20he%20expected%20far%20better%20roles%20to%20be%20created%20in%20their%20place.%20Last%20year%2C%20Altman%20told%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2025%2F07%2F23%2Fsam-altman-artificial-intelligence-too-cheap-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFederal%20Reserve%20conference%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bentire%20classes%26quot%3B%20of%20jobs%20would%20vanish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20is%20not%20the%20only%20one%20to%20have%20issued%20blunt%20warnings%20about%20the%20impact%20of%20AI%20on%20the%20workforce.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ceo-warning-ai-could-eliminate-jobs-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnthropic%20CEO%20Dario%20Amodei%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20last%20May%20that%20AI%20could%20eliminate%20around%2050%25%20of%20entry-level%20office%20jobs%2C%20and%20a%20report%20from%20analyst%20firm%20Citrini%20predicting%20an%20AI-fuelled%20market%20crash%20and%20recession%20sent%20stocks%20tumbling%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20predictions%20of%20an%20AI-fuelled%20jobs%20apocalypse%20have%20failed%20to%20come%20to%20pass%2C%20although%20tech%20companies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-layoffs-memos-share-common-themes-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EBlock%2C%20Snap%2C%20and%20Meta%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20cited%20the%20technology%20in%20recent%20layoff%20announcements.%20In%20February%2C%20Altman%20said%20some%20companies%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ai-washing-layoffs-job-cuts-openai-india-summit-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblaming%20AI%20for%20layoffs%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20would've%20happened%20anyway%2C%20but%20did%20not%20identify%20any%20by%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAltman%20told%20the%20Commonwealth%20Bank%20conference%20that%20he%20thought%20it%20was%20important%20that%20AI%20companies%20be%20frank%20about%20their%20concerns%20around%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20technology%2C%20even%20if%20those%20concerns%20later%20proved%20to%20be%20incorrect.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20believe%20that%20so%20much%20of%20society%20here%20is%20going%20to%20be%20impacted%20by%20this%2C%20that%20we%20are%20all%20stakeholders%2C%20and%20it%20is%20better%20for%20us%20to%20be%20going%20in%20the%20direction%20of%20too%20much%20transparency%20and%20occasionally%20being%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Altman%20said%2C%20according%20to%20the%20summary%20shared%20by%20the%20bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-ai-jobs-prediction-wrong-white-collar-openai-australia-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779800690000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a158b01b1025a62a5c8727a%3F