%2F131327797.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fwhat-looked-like-ordinary-rubble-on-a-university-campus-turned-out-to-be-a-6700-year-old-native-american-artefact%2Farticleshow%2F131327797.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fwhat-looked-like-ordinary-rubble-on-a-university-campus-turned-out-to-be-a-6700-year-old-native-american-artefact%2Famp_articleshow%2F131327797.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fwhat-looked-like-ordinary-rubble-on-a-university-campus-turned-out-to-be-a-6700-year-old-native-american-artefact%2Famp_articleshow%2F131327797.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22My%20mom%20with%20Parkinson's%20moved%20in%20with%20my%20family.%20Eventually%2C%20it%20became%20too%20much%20to%20care%20for%20her.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223088%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20family%20of%20five%2C%20including%20two%20young%20boys%20and%20their%20grandma.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1087647ff506e273e66a85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERachel%20Stein%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20sons%2C%20and%20mom.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Stein%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERachel%20Stein's%20mother%20didn't%20enjoy%20assisted%20living.%20She%20ended%20up%20moving%20in%20with%20her%20family.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20daughter%20cared%20for%20her%20mom%2C%20but%20found%20herself%20pulled%20in%20separate%20directions%20because%20of%20her%20sons.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20and%20her%20mom%20decided%20that%20her%20mom%20should%20return%20to%20assisted%20living%20and%20receive%20professional%20care.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20story%20is%20based%20on%20an%20interview%20with%20Rachel%20Stein%2C%2044%2C%20a%20senior%20vice%20president%20at%20a%20healthcare%20communications%20firm%2C%20from%20Orange%20County%2C%20California.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%2078-year-old%20mom%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fearly-onset-parkinsons-diagnosis-what-happens-next-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EParkinson's%20Disease%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20decade%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20she%20was%20able%20to%20stay%20in%20her%20townhouse.%20As%20the%20illness%20progressed%2C%20however%2C%20she%20started%20having%20a%20hard%20time%20taking%20care%20of%20herself%20and%20preparing%20meals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20concern%20was%20that%20she%20might%20fall%20while%20going%20up%20and%20down%20the%20stairs.%20In%202021%2C%20we%20mutually%20decided%20that%20she%20would%20move%20into%20an%20assisted%20living%20facility%20a%20short%20drive%20from%20our%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20cost%20around%20%247%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20but%20Mom%2C%20who%20had%20worked%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-social-worker-to-become-freelancer-making-six-figures-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esocial%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20lucky%20to%20have%20the%20retirement%20funds%20to%20cover%20the%20fees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b178e8d4-32f2-4b00-9fa3-5521457b78bd%5C%22%3EShe%20wanted%20peace%20and%20quiet%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20didn't%20like%20the%20place%20at%20all%2C%20partly%20because%20it%20was%20too%20large%20and%20overwhelming%20with%20160%20other%20residents.%20She%20often%20got%20tired%20%E2%80%94%20a%20symptom%20of%20her%20illness%20%E2%80%94%20and%20wanted%20peace%20and%20quiet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20your%20situation%20regarding%20long-term%20care%20for%20yourself%20or%20your%20loved%20ones%3F%20To%20share%20your%20story%20with%20a%20Business%20Insider%20reporter%2C%20please%20fill%20out%20this%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdg4AoiQ9q9GU2sU75z7cCrHvjt0JnM_0Nf34JYn_1DpF3w6A%2Fviewform%3Fusp%3Ddialog%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Equick%20form%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20was%20horrible%2C%20and%20she%20was%20unable%20to%20do%20any%20of%20the%20activities%20she%20was%20paying%20for%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freference%2Fbenefits-of-swimming%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eusing%20the%20pool%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMom%20would%20sometimes%20hint%2C%20saying%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I%20wish%20I%20could%20live%20with%20you%20guys.%26quot%3B%20We%20put%20it%20aside%20until%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20when%20I%20realized%20she%20was%20starting%20to%20get%20a%20little%20bit%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wanted%20her%20to%20spend%20the%20time%20she%20had%20left%20with%20me%2C%20my%20husband%2C%20and%20my%20two%20sons%2C%20ages%2012%20and%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20fortunate%20to%20have%20enough%20space%20in%20our%20home.%20But%20her%20bedroom%20was%20upstairs%2C%20so%20she%20still%20had%20to%20tackle%20the%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20in%20a%20heightened%20state%20of%20worry%20that%20she'd%20fall.%20The%20boys%2C%20like%20other%20kids%2C%20would%20leave%20things%20around%20the%20house%20that%20could%20trip%20her.%20If%20they%20took%20a%20shower%20and%20left%20water%20on%20the%20floor%2C%20I%20would%20rush%20inside%20to%20dry%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20dog%2C%20Zoe%2C%20was%20quite%20big%20and%20jumped%20up%2C%20and%20I%20was%20afraid%20she'd%20knock%20her%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20older%20woman%20sitting%20on%20a%20bed%20petting%20a%20black%20dog.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a10aee87ff506e273e66e0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStein's%20mom%20with%20the%20family%20dog%2C%20Zoe.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Stein%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20incredibly%20stressful.%20I%20work%20full%20time%20from%20home%20and%20would%20be%20on%20a%20conference%20call%2C%20and%20Mom%20would%20need%20something%20or%20fall.%20At%20one%20point%2C%20we%20joked%20that%20she%20qualified%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fways-airport-layovers-better-tips-frequent-traveler%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efrequent%20flyer%20%3C%2Fa%3Eat%20the%20ER%20because%20she%20was%20there%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20that%2C%20but%20I%20was%20being%20pulled%20between%20two%20worlds.%20It%20was%20hard%20to%20strike%20a%20balance%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20have%20time%20or%20energy%20to%20be%20completely%20present%20as%20a%20wife%2C%20mother%2C%20and%20carer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20moments%20when%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BWho%20is%20asking%20the%20loudest%3F%26quot%3B%20and%20was%20forced%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20tend%20to%20Mom%20or%20the%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20say%20to%20them%2C%20%26quot%3BHey%2C%20guys%2C%20you%20can%20get%20your%20own%20water%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20my%20mom%20couldn't%20do%20the%20same.%20She%20was%20dependent%20on%20us%2C%20and%20the%20onus%20was%20mostly%20on%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225790191c-64a4-43e6-9fc2-aa3b61838c29%5C%22%3EMy%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%20suffered%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20definitely%20put%20a%20strain%20on%20my%20relationship%20with%20Mom.%20I%20loved%20her%20very%20much%2C%20but%20we%20both%20got%20frustrated%20at%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20eventually%20brought%20in%20some%20carers%20to%20walk%20with%20her%2C%20make%20some%20of%20her%20meals%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-needs-friends-wearable-ai-friend-companion-review-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eprovide%20companionship%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20were%20great%2C%20but%20the%20help%20wasn't%20nearly%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20sister%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoving-to-canada-from-us-cost-of-living-higher-happier-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elives%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20came%20to%20visit%20in%20February%202026.%20She%20saw%20how%20much%20worse%20Mom%20had%20gotten.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20how%20you%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20I'm%20doing%20it%20well%2C%20and%20it's%20becoming%20a%20challenge%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20replied.%20Her%20care%20needs%20were%20beyond%20what%20my%20mental%20and%20physical%20health%20could%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20older%20woman%20and%20her%20daughter.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a10af6551ede568c7e17bfe%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221737%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStein%20and%20her%20mother%20at%20the%20assisted%20living%20facility.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rachel%20Stein%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20soft-sounded%20Mom%20and%2C%20though%20she%20wasn't%20too%20happy%20about%20the%20idea%20at%20first%2C%20looked%20for%20another%20assisted%20living%20facility%20together%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20one%20we%20chose%20was%20entirely%20different%20from%20the%20first.%20It%20was%20much%20smaller%2C%20with%20a%20little%20over%2070%20residents%2C%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20ladies%20approached%20us%2C%20unsolicited%2C%20and%20said%20how%20much%20they%20liked%20the%20place.%20We%20tried%20the%20food%2C%20which%20was%20really%20tasty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226ac0cb4f-047d-4825-81a8-8ea04dca0052%5C%22%3EWe%20now%20have%20breathing%20room%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMom%20moved%20out%20at%20the%20end%20of%20March.%20She%20received%20the%20care%20she%20needed%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-shortage-hiring-outlook-skill-gap-job-market-chamber-commerce-2021-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Equalified%20workers%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20help%20getting%20in%20and%20out%20of%20bed%20and%20walking%20to%20the%20bathroom%20%E2%80%94%20and%20was%20recently%20transferred%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhospice-nurse-tiktok-influencer-love-job-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehospice%20care%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20visit%20her%20regularly%20on%20my%20own%20or%20with%20the%20family.%20It's%20good%20to%20see%20her%20settled%2C%20and%20I%20can%20spend%20quality%20time%20with%20the%20kids.%20My%20husband%20remarked%20that%20they%20don't%20fight%20as%20much%20as%20they%20used%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20given%20us%20all%20breathing%20room.%20Having%20their%20grandmother%20at%20home%20was%20workable%20%E2%80%94%20until%20it%20wasn't.%20Circumstances%20changed%2C%20and%20the%20family%20agreed%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Mom%20%E2%80%94%20that%20we%20were%20doing%20the%20right%20thing%20for%20her%20and%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaring-for-mom-with-parkinsons-at-home-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1779793681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a1087647ff506e273e66a85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaring-for-mom-with-parkinsons-at-home-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rachel%20Stein%20says%20caring%20for%20her%20mother%20with%20Parkinson's%20at%20home%20became%20emotionally%20and%20physically%20overwhelming%20for%20the%20entire%20family.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Jane%20Ridley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3